{
  "texts": [
    "It holds the potential to reactivate and promote brain healing.The findings of our study revealed that VR-based games have been more effective in improving cognitive disorders compared to VR-based educational programs.",
    "Liu et al. 's study [66] demonstrated significant improvements in the Montreal Cognitive Assessment (MoCA), Trail-Making Test-A (TMT-A), Digit Symbol Substitution Test (DSST), Digital Span Test (DST), Verbal Fluency Test (VFT), and Modified Barthel Index (MBI) following the use of VRbased puzzle games by stroke patients.",
    "Yang-Kun et al. [67], demonstrated that VR-based games enhance children's cognitive performance, including attention, critical thinking, abstract reasoning, and information processing.",
    "Yanguas et al. 's study [68] similarly exhibited cognitive function improvement through the utilization of VRbased games.",
    "VR-based games offer users a captivating experience by incorporating features such as interactive screens, touch controllers, motion sensors, voice notifications, physical vibrations, omnidirectional vision, and engaging gameplay elements like collecting points and defending against enemies."
  ]
}